                "index_texts": [
                    "Press enter or click to view image in full sizeMATHEMATICAL MYSTERIESThe Strange Case of Gabriel\u2019s HornThere is a peculiar trumpet in mathematics.It is not made of brass or wood. It is not something you can hold or hear. It exists only as an exact mathematical construction, defined by a simple equation. And yet, despite its simplicity, it behaves in a way that feels almost impossible.Imagine this horn stretching out into space, longer and longer, becoming thinner and thinner, never quite ending.Now consider this. If I gave you a gallon of paint, you could pour it inside and fill it completely.But if I asked you to paint its outer surface, even all the paint in the world would not be enough.The same object can be filled with a finite amount of paint, and at the same time requires an infinite amount to cover.That is the paradox of Gabriel\u2019s horn.The object that should not existWe begin with a very simple graph.Press enter or click to view image in full sizeGraph of y = 1/x (red) together with the vertical line x = 1 (blue). The portion of the curve for x \u2265 1 is used to generate Gabriel\u2019s horn by rotation about the x-axis."
                ],
